snippet.textDisplay:
The truth is, Atletico Madrid outperform Liverpool in every aspect of the game except the ball possession. So, to say Atletico won because Liverpool has an off day is a blatant excuse. Liverpool tried their best but they were outplayed like I said, that is why they look bad, they look off.. they were outplayed, I repeat.

Second leg it's a 50-50, not Liverpool as the favorite. I know it's Anfield.. but imagine a situation where Atletico score another away goal with just 25% of ball possession in a counter attack (as you can see in the first leg, that that is a possibility), Liverpool have to score 3 goals to progress, and that's a lot to do even for Liverpool, one of the best attacking side ATM. So you never know. Be confident but don't overdo it. Barcelona type of miracle doesn't happen every year.

snippet.textDisplay:
Just watched the entire thing back. My verdict is that this is the first match in which we played the entire 94+ minutes at the opposition's level, complete with being suckered into all the dirty tricks and wind-ups. A timely warning and wake-up call that must be heeded. We are far too naïve when opponents resort to the dark arts and end being frustratingly lured into stupid bookings. It's telling that Klopp had to sub Mané to save him from what would most certainly have been a sending off. I would hate to see us ever base our game on the dark arts to the insane degree Atleti do, but we must learn to rid ourselves of the naïvety.
Get back on the winning path, you beautiful Mighty Reds! YNWA
